def explore_data(df):
    print(" 5   :")
    display(df.head())
    
    print("\n   :")
    display(df.info())
    
    print("\n   :")
    display(df.describe(include='all').T)
    
    print("\n     :")
    for column in df.columns:
        unique_values = df[column].unique()
        num_unique_values = len(unique_values)
        print(f" '{column}'  {num_unique_values}  .")
    
    print("\n      :")
    for column in df.columns:
        if df[column].dtype == 'object':
            value_counts = df[column].value_counts()
            print(f" '{column}':")
            print(value_counts)
            
    print("\n   :")
    df.hist(figsize=(25, 25))

def check_missing_duplicates(df):

    #    'date'
    df.sort_values('date', inplace=True)

    #   'date'  
    #df.set_index('date', inplace=True)

    #  
    missing_values = df.isnull().sum()
    if missing_values.sum() > 0:
        print(" :")
        print(missing_values)
    else:
        print("  .")

    #  
    duplicate_rows = df.duplicated()
    if duplicate_rows.sum() > 0:
        print(" :")
        print(df[duplicate_rows])
    else:
        print("  .")

    #     
    df_filled = df.interpolate(method='time')

    #     
    missing_values_filled = df_filled.isnull().sum()
    if missing_values_filled.sum() > 0:
        print("  :")
        print(missing_values_filled)
    else:
        print("  .")

    #    'date'
    df_filled.reset_index(inplace=True)

    return df_filled

def detect_and_print_outliers(df, threshold=3):
    final_i = None
    outliers = {}

    for column in df.columns:
        if pd.api.types.is_numeric_dtype(df[column]):
            total_rows = df[column].copy().shape[0]
            q1 = df[column].quantile(0.25)
            q3 = df[column].quantile(0.75)
            iqr = q3 - q1
            lower_bound = q1 - threshold * iqr
            upper_bound = q3 + threshold * iqr

            column_outliers = df[(df[column] < lower_bound) | (df[column] > upper_bound)]
            num_outliers = column_outliers.shape[0]

            outlier_ratio = (num_outliers / total_rows) * 100

            outliers[column] = {
                'num_outliers': num_outliers,
                'outlier_ratio': outlier_ratio
            }

    result_df = pd.DataFrame(outliers).T
    result_df.index.name = ''
    result_df.columns = [' ', '  (%)']

    result_df = result_df.sort_values('  (%)', ascending=False)
    
    #      
    pd.set_option('display.max_rows', 86)

    display(result_df)

def remove_rows_with_zero(df):
    original_size = df.shape[0]  #   

    df_cleaned = df.loc[(df != 0).all(axis=1)] #     
    df_cleaned.reset_index(drop=True, inplace=True)  #  

    cleaned_size = df_cleaned.shape[0]  #   

    reduction_percentage = (original_size - cleaned_size) / original_size * 100  #   

    print(f"  : {original_size}")
    print(f"  : {cleaned_size}")
    print(f" : {reduction_percentage}%")

    return df_cleaned

Функция для вычисления итоговой sMAPE¶

In [27]:
def sMAPE(y_true, y_pred):
    return np.mean( np.abs( y_pred - y_true ) / (np.abs( y_pred + y_true ) / 2) ) * 100


def total_sMAPE(y_true, y_pred):
    y_true_rougher = y_true['rougher.output.recovery']
    y_true_final = y_true['final.output.recovery']
    y_pred_rougher = y_pred[:, 0]  #   rougher.output.recovery
    y_pred_final = y_pred[:, 1]  #   final.output.recovery
    
    sMAPE_rougher = sMAPE(y_true_rougher, y_pred_rougher)
    sMAPE_final = sMAPE(y_true_final, y_pred_final)
    
    total_sMAPE = 0.25 * sMAPE_rougher + 0.75 * sMAPE_final
    
    return total_sMAPE
